/* 938 — cb_conv differential oracle, build-gated (W2.2 / ENHANCE-21 / SEPARATE-2).
 *
 * The first-order SKI combinator conversion (cb_conv) and the kernel's CCL-backed NbE
 * conversion (tc_conv) must AGREE on a fixed, comprehensive corpus of conversion pairs
 * spanning the computational fragment (beta, Bool/Nat/sum/Id iota, constructor
 * distinctness) -- positive AND negative arms.  99 = every pair agrees; any other code =
 * the 1-based index of the first pair where the two independent reduction engines diverge,
 * which would expose a soundness bug in the trusted reducer.  Part of run_corpus GREEN: any
 * ccl edit that diverges cb_conv from tc_conv reddens the build. */
module corpus_938
extern @abi(c-msvc-x64) fn cb_differential_cert() -> u64 from "typecheck.iii"
fn main() -> u64 { return cb_differential_cert() }
